SENATE RESOLUTION 234
By Yarbro
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Lillie Cate Allen, 2025
Salutatorian of Hillsboro High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Lillie Cate Allen is one such exceptional student who was recently named
Salutatorian of the 2025 graduating class at Hillsboro High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Allen has achieved outstanding academic success
and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country; and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Lillie Allen has earned an exemplary
grade point average while participating in a number of extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, her display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for her
future success; and
WHEREAS, Lillie Allen's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
her family, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Allen's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of our respect,
admiration, and commendation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby commend and honor
the 2025 Hillsboro High School Salutatorian, Lillie Cate Allen, on her impressive academic
achievement and extend to her our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
